<h3>About Me</h3>

Qifeng Chen is an Associate Professor at the Hong Kong University of Science and Technology. He earned his PhD in Computer Science from Stanford University. His research interests include generative AI, computational photography, and autonomous driving. Recognized for his contributions to the field, he was named one of the "35 Innovators Under 35" and one of the top 100 AI young pioneers in China by MIT Technology Review. For his innovative research in image enhancement, he received the Google Faculty Research Award. Additionally, he has served as an area chair for international conferences, including CVPR, NeurIPS, ICCV, ACM Multimedia, and IJCAI.